I wasn't thinking of altering OpenSSL; more like calling mlock() in a CKey member.

```
CKey()
{
    pkey = EC_KEY_new_by_curve_name(NID_secp256k1);
    if (pkey == NULL)
        throw key_error("CKey::CKey() : EC_KEY_new_by_curve_name failed");
    mlock( pkey, sizeof( *pkey ) );
    fSet = false;
}
```

But that's not going to work because EC_KEY isn't an exported structure, so sizeof() won't work; nor is there any way to see what internal memory structures in EC_KEY have been allocated.

Bah.

Someone else must have solved this already.  I'll have a search.

